rity, the online world, and the appeal of sexual intimacy.  In From Single to Serious, Dana M. Malone shines a light on friendship, dating, and, sexuality, in both the ideals and the practical experiences of heterosexual students at U. S. evangelical colleges. She examines the struggles they have in balancing their gendered and religious presentations of self, the expectations of their campus community, and their desire to find meaningful romantic relationships.     aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4acollege religion. 4acollege sex. 4acollege students. 4acollege. 4adating. 4aevangelical. 4afriendship. 4ahook up. 4aintimacy. 4apurity. 4arelationship. 4areligion. 4aromance. 4asex. 4avirgin. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017-2018z978311065742508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018z978311066608340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813587912423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813587912.jpg  a978-3-11-065742-5  RUP eBook-Package 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066330-3  RUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-066608-3  RUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG